Pakistan beat West Indies by 170 runs in first Test 
Pakistan defeated the West Indies by 170 runs in the first cricket Test
here on Monday to take a 1-0 lead in the two-match series.
Needing 342 to win, the West Indies were shot out for 171 in their
second innings just before tea on the fifth and final day at the
Sharjah cricket stadium.
The second Test starts at the same venue on Thursday.
